title: Balls secures a Pentakill in unexpected win against Fnatic
body: The first Pentakill of Worlds 2015 belongs to Cloud9's top laner An "Balls" Le!

Yamato at the beginning predicted that Cloud 9 would go 0-6, and Monte has predicted they would lose every game. It just makes me giggle
Yeah but at least Yamato conceded his statement and admitted they're good like the rest of the casters. For some reason Monte just really, really doesn't like C9
Actually Monte likes C9. He just probably didn't expect them as most did, to do well. I believe he doesn't like TSM.

No idea where you get that impression. I have seen Monte be rude to C9 publicly on multiple occasions since 2014. His rant about C9 being a "bad team" at the start of worlds before they played was absolutely hilarious. It was so disrespectful not only towards C9 but to NA as a whole. He attempted to discredit the whole thing by saying that C9 was a bad team, and also went on to say the teams they faced were weak. I don't think so. C9 is absolutely _KILLING_ it right now. NA and EU are looking like much more competitive regions overall than both Korea and China (although I still think the top two teams are SKT/EDG). Liquid, TIP? Both solid teams in their own right IMO and well fought by C9. It's true, they grow stronger every match, but they looked good still even in the gauntlet. The best part? I'm right. F U MONTE

I cannot believe C9 will be the no.1 heading into quarter final.
there's no guarantee yet... still 3 more games

But they would need quite the spectacular f**k up to not make it out of groups. All they need to do is win one game and they're locked in a tiebreaker for first (and that's assuming someone else wiins all their remaining games) no matter how well any of the other teams do. Even if they LOSE all their remaining games, which seems very unlikely, they'd be tied for second.
You say that, but if TL had won one game in the last weeks of the Summer Split, C9 wouldn't even have gotten to the gauntlet.
And yet... here we are with C9 3 - 0 at Worlds.
I believe C9 will be the no.1 since C9 take everyone's energy

So long as C9 can come up with more stratagies than just the sieging team comp, they should be fine. I know the teams will look to take advantage of it next week by keeping them off {{champion:18}}  or {{champion:268}} , so hopefully they have more stratagies to fall back on. If they can do that then i'm sure they will end the group 5-1 at least and maybe 6-0 if they can keep improving.

This is the best we've seen Cloud 9 play in a long, long time. They couldn't have picked a better setting to turn on the afterburners and kick it into high gear, either. This was a team that the analyst desk predicted to go 0 -6 and called a "bad team." They're not the most dominant North American showing at Worlds right now, toppling the likes of Fnatic. How many times have we heard that Europe completely trashes North America? How many times have we heard that Cloud 9 is washed up? This is probably the most dominant performance any North American team has had on the international stage, and I hope Monte takes a moment to reflect on what an ass Cloud 9 has made him look like.
